  "text": "Soft-tissue hematomas can occur in the presence of bleeding diathesis, anticoagulant therapy, surgery, or trauma, and rarely occur spontaneously. In the majority of cases, softtissue hematomas present acutely and resolve spontaneously, but sometimes, they present as swellings that slowly expand. In such cases, CEH may be suspected and can be mistaken for a soft-tissue neoplasm [CITATION_1] .",
